         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Toorak ¶ 24th July 1861 ¶ My dear Dr Mueller, ¶  ¶ I return your letter to Sir William Hooker. ¶  I think your offer in regard to Mr Bentham's proposed Flora of Australia is most generous and liberal,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.07.24a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Henry Barkly</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Directors' letters, vol. LXXV, Australian and Pacific letters 1859-65, letter no. 12.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black edged.</p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is presumably the letter from Barkly that M enclosed with the letter he wrote to William Hooker on 25 July 1861 (in the edition as 61-07-25a).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Toorak</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24th July 1861</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Dr Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I return your letter to Sir William Hooker.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M to W. Hooker, 23 July 1861.</p>
               </note> I think your offer in regard to Mr Bentham's proposed Flora of Australia is most generous and liberal, &amp; I will give it every support in writing to Sir William.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See H. Barkly to W. Hooker 24 July 1861 (in this edition as M61-07-24).</p>
               </note> I am too busy at the moment in preparing for the Mail to say more.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have read the letters which you kindly encl[osed] &amp; send them back with thanks.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letters not identified.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">[Ever] [faithfully]</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Barkly.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
